a gun to a knife fight.

03:38.043 --> 03:39.044
[SWORD SCRAPES]

03:42.831 --> 03:44.746
Knoxville, Tennessee.

03:46.182 --> 03:49.446
Waitressing,
substitute teaching.

03:49.490 --> 03:50.926
Whatever.

03:52.449 --> 03:55.409
My real job was rum and Cokes
and making bad choices.

03:55.452 --> 03:57.280
[SNIFFS AND CHUCKLES]

03:58.063 --> 04:00.414
Sleeping with cops,

04:00.457 --> 04:01.937
dealing weed
to eighth graders.

04:05.506 --> 04:07.247
I was lost.

04:09.684 --> 04:11.468
Until I met Klaus.

04:14.602 --> 04:17.822
Saw his strength,

04:19.476 --> 04:21.957
his humorless cruelty,
and I...

04:28.180 --> 04:29.660
I was lost all over again.

04:29.704 --> 04:31.096
TULIP: Oh, yeah.

04:31.140 --> 04:34.752
Nothing like humorless
cruelty to get you going.

04:34.796 --> 04:35.797
Shut up!

04:39.888 --> 04:44.458
I am so sick and tired
of you nonbelievers.

04:44.501 --> 04:48.070
Smoking and smirking.

04:48.113 --> 04:49.985
And just thinking
of themselves

04:50.028 --> 04:51.682
and what
they're gonna get.

04:51.726 --> 04:53.989
Well, you don't have
to think anymore

04:54.032 --> 04:57.471
'cause when the righteous
lays down with the wicked,

04:59.777 --> 05:01.649
this is what they get.

05:01.692 --> 05:03.172
[CLICKING]

05:05.479 --> 05:07.916
[SCREAMS IN FRUSTRATION]

05:10.092 --> 05:11.572
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

05:15.010 --> 05:17.360
Damn it, Sarah.
You can't do
anything right.

05:19.144 --> 05:20.145
Uh...

05:22.322 --> 05:23.627
May I?
[SNIFFLES]

05:26.282 --> 05:27.414
[CRYING]

05:30.895 --> 05:33.507
Sometimes,
with the SIG Sauer,

05:33.550 --> 05:35.247
when the firing pin
gets hot... [BLOWS]

05:36.161 --> 05:37.293
It jams, I know.

05:41.428 --> 05:44.387
True what you say
about selfishness
in the world.

05:44.431 --> 05:45.867
Sometimes,

05:45.910 --> 05:49.914
doing what's right for you,
and just you,

05:49.958 --> 05:54.049
no cause, no religion,
no man,

05:54.876 --> 05:56.617
it ain't selfish at all.

05:59.010 --> 06:01.143
Sometimes,

06:01.186 --> 06:03.101
it's just righteous.

06:07.062 --> 06:09.543
Now, this is fixed.

06:09.586 --> 06:11.501
But I'm
gonna keep it.

06:12.589 --> 06:14.156
I got tons of them.

06:32.130 --> 06:33.131
Aah!

06:38.833 --> 06:40.225
[CHIRPING]

06:40.269 --> 06:42.271
STARR: Still not working.

06:42.314 --> 06:44.404
[MAN SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY
OVER PHONE]

06:44.447 --> 06:48.364
No, there's no time
for an in-house service call.

06:48.408 --> 06:50.801
The world
is ending today.

06:52.542 --> 06:56.546
Don't put me on hold again.
No, Adnan...

06:56.590 --> 06:58.896
Are you listening?
I said don't put me on...

06:58.940 --> 07:01.856
Adnan? Adnan?

07:01.899 --> 07:03.510
[PLAYING FLUTE]

07:07.427 --> 07:09.559
Hey, you're, uh...
Yeah.

07:09.603 --> 07:12.083
Big fan. So is my wife.
Honey, say hello.

07:12.127 --> 07:13.868
It's just
such a pleasure.

07:13.911 --> 07:16.305
The pleasure is mine.

07:16.348 --> 07:18.350
Hey, while I have you,
let me bend
your ear a minute

07:18.394 --> 07:20.396
'cause I got
a lot of questions.

07:23.051 --> 07:24.574
ANNOUNCER: Now,
ladies and gentlemen,

07:24.618 --> 07:28.317
the moment
we've been waiting for,
for 2,000 years.

07:28.360 --> 07:29.797
[LOUD CHEERING]

07:29.840 --> 07:32.408
The Messiah!

07:32.452 --> 07:34.062
[CHEERING CONTINUES]

07:35.193 --> 07:36.281
Showtime.

07:37.457 --> 07:38.458
Uh...

07:40.068 --> 07:41.504
Look, I don't
like it either,

07:41.548 --> 07:43.027
but this is the deal.
So come on.

07:43.375 --> 07:44.768
Uh...

07:44.812 --> 07:47.641
Don't give me that.
They were gonna kill you.

07:48.206 --> 07:49.207
Uh, no.

07:50.208 --> 07:51.209
Come on.

07:52.341 --> 07:54.256
You can't hide
in the clothes.No.

07:54.299 --> 07:57.041
Don't hide in the clothes.
No.

07:57.999 --> 07:59.391
Get out!

07:59.435 --> 08:02.046
[WHIMPERING]

08:02.090 --> 08:04.484
Now. They're all
gonna die anyway.
Come on.

08:05.659 --> 08:06.834
[GRUNTING]

08:09.184 --> 08:10.925
What are you
doing, Cass?

08:16.496 --> 08:17.497
[GUNSHOT]

08:19.890 --> 08:21.762
[GUNSHOTS]

08:30.031 --> 08:31.162
Die! [GRUNTS]

08:38.126 --> 08:39.127
[YELLS]

08:46.961 --> 08:48.702
Come on!

08:48.745 --> 08:51.139
Hippie wimp!
Fascist pig.

08:51.182 --> 08:52.444
[YELLS]

09:07.721 --> 09:08.678
[COCKS GUN]

09:21.169 --> 09:22.562
[STEADY BEEPING]

09:22.605 --> 09:24.389
WOMAN: [ON PA] Dr. Rodell
to the burn unit.

09:24.433 --> 09:27.001
Dr. Rodell
to the burn unit.MAN: Okay, he's waking up.

09:27.044 --> 09:29.264
Let's remove the bandages.

09:30.918 --> 09:35.270
Hello there, mate.
You've had an accident.

09:35.313 --> 09:38.447
The bad news is,
you've suffered
some facial trauma.

09:38.490 --> 09:40.710
But the good news is,
you're gonna be fine.

09:40.754 --> 09:43.278
Nurse, could you, uh,
could you get the mirror?

09:43.321 --> 09:45.541
Plastic surgeons here
have been working
day and night.

09:45.585 --> 09:47.674
Called you
their passion project.

09:47.717 --> 09:53.288
So we're all
just a little bit curious
to see what...

09:53.331 --> 09:54.681
Oh, my God.

09:54.724 --> 09:56.596
[NURSE GASPS AND SCREAMS]

09:56.639 --> 09:59.990
Have some respect, people.
It's still a human being!

10:00.600 --> 10:01.862
[WOMAN SCREAMS]

10:05.648 --> 10:06.736
[SIGHS HEAVILY]

10:10.784 --> 10:11.741
[THUDS]

10:18.922 --> 10:19.923
Aah!

10:24.798 --> 10:25.755
[CHRISTINA YELLS]

10:27.104 --> 10:28.105
[GROANS]

10:32.414 --> 10:35.417
Oh, he got me.
Right in the pancreas.

10:35.460 --> 10:36.679
But you'll come back
to life, right?

10:37.114 --> 10:38.202
[GROANS]

10:39.639 --> 10:41.684
I shat myself.

10:41.728 --> 10:43.817
[GROANS]

10:43.860 --> 10:46.776
I haven't done that since...
He can't kill you.

10:46.820 --> 10:49.561
I think that boy...
He can kill anything.

10:51.868 --> 10:54.741
Our baby. Our baby.

10:54.784 --> 10:57.787
You do the right thing.
Yeah. And what is that?

10:57.831 --> 10:58.788
[CHRISTINA SCREAMS]

10:59.223 --> 11:00.529
Sweetheart!

11:01.269 --> 11:02.487
Genesis...

11:02.531 --> 11:03.924
[BREATHING HEAVILY]

11:07.667 --> 11:08.711
[GUNSHOTS]

11:15.587 --> 11:17.764
[GRUNTING]

11:30.254 --> 11:31.255
Oh.

11:36.391 --> 11:37.827
All right.

11:40.221 --> 11:41.265
[GRUNTS]

11:42.353 --> 11:43.485
You win.

11:47.968 --> 11:50.274
Goodbye, Preacher.

11:50.318 --> 11:51.319
[COCKS GUN]

11:54.757 --> 11:55.889
You hear that?

11:57.281 --> 11:59.153
Peace and quiet.

12:03.984 --> 12:07.291
Family picnics,
planting a garden.

12:08.379 --> 12:09.990
That's what he's offering.

12:11.992 --> 12:13.471
And that's what you want.

12:16.344 --> 12:17.475
So go on.

12:19.608 --> 12:23.394
One last kill,

12:27.268 --> 12:29.444
if that's really
what you want.

12:36.407 --> 12:37.539
[BOTH GRUNTING]

12:42.762 --> 12:46.156
If he lives,
everyone dies.

12:48.245 --> 12:49.943
You get that, right?

12:49.986 --> 12:51.031
It's not my problem.

12:52.119 --> 12:53.076
[HUMPERDOO WHIMPERS]

12:54.295 --> 12:55.905
Hump, go and wait
in the clothes.

12:55.949 --> 12:57.907
TULIP: What the hell
is wrong with you?

12:57.951 --> 12:58.908
Hmm?

13:00.780 --> 13:01.868
Jesse?

13:03.434 --> 13:05.219
I love him.

13:05.262 --> 13:07.003
Ever since
I was a little kid.

13:07.525 --> 13:09.136
I never stopped.

13:09.963 --> 13:11.660
He came back and...

13:11.703 --> 13:12.966
[SIGHS]

13:13.009 --> 13:16.056
I get that that sucks
a little bit for you.

13:16.099 --> 13:17.797
I get it.

13:17.840 --> 13:21.278
But you wanna blow up
the whole world
'cause of it?

13:21.322 --> 13:24.586
Wise up, quit acting
like a baby, and move!

13:26.675 --> 13:27.981
Move!

13:34.552 --> 13:36.816
What do you
want me to say, huh?

13:36.859 --> 13:38.556
You're my best friend.

13:38.600 --> 13:40.863
No one, and I mean no one,

13:40.907 --> 13:42.386
makes me laugh like you do.

13:43.518 --> 13:45.607
And you know I love you,
but...

13:45.650 --> 13:47.522
Only when I'm sad.

13:48.566 --> 13:50.307
And I need a little shag.

13:55.486 --> 13:57.010
You've hit me a lot.

13:58.054 --> 13:59.969
And, honestly, I let it go

14:00.013 --> 14:00.970
because I love you.

14:02.972 --> 14:04.931
So I just let you hurt me.

14:04.974 --> 14:07.107
But I am so done.

14:07.150 --> 14:09.500
And if you hit me
like that again,

14:10.197 --> 14:11.415
honestly, I'm gonna

14:11.459 --> 14:12.547
fucking kill you.

14:16.812 --> 14:18.031
I'm sorry.

14:23.166 --> 14:25.690
MAN: First I'm hearing it,
you know?
You're my best friend.

14:25.734 --> 14:28.171
You think it's okay
to try and grab-ass
my wife?

14:28.215 --> 14:30.260
Henry, he didn't grab-ass.
He just sent me a text.

14:30.304 --> 14:31.827
That's not even
the worst of it.

14:31.871 --> 14:33.220
Next, he tries
to tell me...

14:36.092 --> 14:39.095
You're disappointed in me.

14:39.139 --> 14:41.054
You're just
another unbeliever.

14:42.577 --> 14:44.274
Stand up
and get on the tarp.

14:44.318 --> 14:48.191
And you believe
what, exactly?

14:48.235 --> 14:50.237
Duty. Service.

14:51.412 --> 14:52.674
Righteousness.

14:52.717 --> 14:56.678
Toiling in a harsh
and hateful life

14:56.721 --> 14:59.159
to be rewarded
in Paradise.

14:59.202 --> 15:03.206
Life is not a thing
to pass through.

15:03.250 --> 15:06.557
Life is the thing itself.

15:08.342 --> 15:09.734
Look there.

15:09.778 --> 15:14.435
The particulates of dust
dancing in the window light.

15:14.478 --> 15:17.481
Nothing very hateful
about that, is there?

15:18.395 --> 15:20.006
I just got off the phone

15:20.049 --> 15:23.574
with a submarine commander
in the Egyptian Navy.

15:23.618 --> 15:28.188
While the world turns to ash,
we'll make our escape.

15:28.231 --> 15:30.930
No. You're getting
on the tarp.

15:33.715 --> 15:35.673
"We"?

15:35.717 --> 15:40.069
We're going to live
under the sea, you and I.

15:40.113 --> 15:45.988
Eating, yoga, talking about
books we like,

15:46.032 --> 15:49.992
pleasuring you repeatedly
with my anus.

15:50.036 --> 15:53.735
I don't think you'll get
that kind of offer
from Paradise.

15:56.999 --> 15:59.959
You are of great value
to me, Flufferman.

16:00.872 --> 16:02.570
And you always have been.

16:14.408 --> 16:15.887
Sorry, sir,

16:16.714 --> 16:19.326
but my name is Featherstone.

16:19.369 --> 16:20.327
[GUNSHOT]

16:26.202 --> 16:27.160
[THUDS]

17:02.978 --> 17:04.806
[TULIP GRUNTING]

17:09.550 --> 17:10.551
[WHIMPERS]

17:21.779 --> 17:23.346
[PEPPY PIANO MUSIC PLAYING]

17:31.137 --> 17:32.747
The clock says zero.

17:34.357 --> 17:36.620
He has to dance.
That's the signal.

17:37.795 --> 17:41.016
ALL: Kill us all!
Kill us all!

17:41.060 --> 17:44.411
Kill us all! Kill us all!

17:44.454 --> 17:45.499
MAN: At the end
of the day,

17:45.542 --> 17:47.501
how many beers you've had
is no excuse.

17:47.544 --> 17:50.852
I wonder where
the Holy Child is?WOMAN: It's been a while.

17:50.895 --> 17:53.724
You know
these performer types.
Want us to beg for it.

17:53.768 --> 17:55.552
Maybe somebody should
check on him.

17:55.596 --> 17:56.727
I'm in the middle
of my story.

17:56.771 --> 17:58.903
Or not.
It's your apocalypse.

17:58.947 --> 18:00.209
You can die
some other day.

18:00.253 --> 18:02.559
I wanna die today.
Let's go.

18:02.603 --> 18:04.953
ALL: Kill us all!
Kill us all!

18:04.996 --> 18:06.476
I'd bring help,

18:07.869 --> 18:11.177
in case
he has stage fright.

18:12.308 --> 18:15.224
ALL: Kill us all!
Kill us all!

18:16.660 --> 18:17.661
[GLASS SHATTERS]

18:19.402 --> 18:20.360
[GRUNTING]

18:44.558 --> 18:45.602
MAN: Messiah?

18:46.647 --> 18:47.865
[KNOCKING ON DOOR]

18:47.909 --> 18:48.997
Messiah?

18:51.478 --> 18:52.435
Messiah?

18:55.960 --> 18:56.961
[THUDS]

18:58.137 --> 18:59.138
MAN: Messiah?

19:00.617 --> 19:01.575
Messiah?
[GUNSHOTS]

19:04.317 --> 19:05.318
[GRUNTS]
[THUDS]

19:06.536 --> 19:07.537
Messiah?

19:09.931 --> 19:11.628
Still think
I'm the funniest?

19:11.672 --> 19:13.717
Messiah? Messiah?

19:13.761 --> 19:17.025
Yeah. I do, actually.

19:19.070 --> 19:20.289
[GRUNTS]

19:28.036 --> 19:29.342
Cass...

19:29.385 --> 19:30.778
I know.

19:30.821 --> 19:31.822
[GRUNTS]

19:32.649 --> 19:34.434
Cass.
I know.

19:35.435 --> 19:36.479
[MAN GRUNTS]

19:36.523 --> 19:37.654
Go away.

19:43.312 --> 19:45.184
So much for second chances.

19:46.881 --> 19:48.317
To the moon.

19:48.361 --> 19:49.318
[GUNSHOT]
[YELPS]

20:22.699 --> 20:25.136
CASSIDY: He was
the best person I ever met.

20:25.180 --> 20:27.791
No bullshit, no agendas.

20:29.619 --> 20:32.535
He liked everyone,
even assholes.

20:37.714 --> 20:41.457
It was the way I'd feel
when I was with him,
you know? [SNIFFLES]

20:41.501 --> 20:43.807
It just felt like...
Like he changed you.

20:47.985 --> 20:50.249
[TEARFULLY]
He was really special.

21:15.709 --> 21:17.276
[BOTH GRUNTING]

21:21.105 --> 21:22.106
Jew!

21:24.631 --> 21:26.110
Jew!

21:26.154 --> 21:28.287
you're goddamn right.

21:29.723 --> 21:31.290
[YELLS]

21:43.911 --> 21:46.566
Dad?
It's time, son.

21:47.349 --> 21:48.437
Finally.

21:49.612 --> 21:51.092
It's time for what?

21:51.135 --> 21:52.398
To...

21:53.181 --> 21:54.835
To be the Messiah.

21:58.534 --> 22:05.585
ALL: [CHANTING] Messiah!
Messiah! Messiah!

22:05.628 --> 22:09.676
Messiah! Messiah!

22:09.719 --> 22:11.721
[BOOING]

22:13.941 --> 22:16.726
I got some bad news
for you people.

22:16.770 --> 22:18.380
[BOOING CONTINUES]

22:20.077 --> 22:21.557
[IN ALTERED VOICE]
So listen up.

22:21.601 --> 22:22.993
[AUDIENCE FALLS SILENT]

22:26.519 --> 22:28.129
You're saying no?

22:29.217 --> 22:30.740
I used to want it.

22:32.176 --> 22:35.179
To be the Savior
for everyone,
like you promised.

22:35.223 --> 22:36.833
I'm just a person,
you know?

22:36.877 --> 22:38.661
No better, no worse
than anybody.

22:38.705 --> 22:42.796
You know I don't
need you, right?

22:42.839 --> 22:46.713
The "Messiah" thing,
it's just... It's...

22:46.756 --> 22:49.106
It's showbiz.

22:49.150 --> 22:50.934
I can blow
the whole thing up myself

22:50.978 --> 22:54.068
at any time for any reason.

22:54.111 --> 22:57.332
Or you could
be merciful.

22:57.376 --> 23:00.422
Mer...
Patient, tolerant, and loving.

23:00.466 --> 23:02.119
[SHOUTS] Loving?

23:02.163 --> 23:06.123
Yeah. And these
three things remain.

23:07.516 --> 23:09.953
Faith, hope, and love.

23:10.780 --> 23:11.999
The greatest of the...

23:22.052 --> 23:24.620
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

23:31.932 --> 23:32.933
Run.

23:45.902 --> 23:47.121
[ENGINE STARTS]

23:58.088 --> 24:00.439
[IN NORMAL VOICE]
The world is not
coming to an end.

24:02.136 --> 24:04.834
Not today anyway.

24:04.878 --> 24:06.880
