God forgive me.
I dearly loved him.

46:53.201 --> 46:54.986
Amen.

46:56.509 --> 46:57.771
Preacher.

46:57.815 --> 46:59.991
He figured you'd
come back here
sometime.

47:00.034 --> 47:04.560
Figured that you and I
had some
unfinished business.

47:06.475 --> 47:07.607
He figured right.

47:10.088 --> 47:11.654
You dare?

47:12.873 --> 47:16.877
It is given unto none
to judge me!

47:16.921 --> 47:18.836
Stand aside!

47:26.060 --> 47:27.018
Uh...

47:31.979 --> 47:36.114
Can you not understand,

47:36.157 --> 47:37.724
William?

47:37.767 --> 47:40.509
Can you know

47:40.553 --> 47:43.773
what it was like
to be the creator

47:44.818 --> 47:47.386
in the time
before creation?

47:51.607 --> 47:53.392
I was alone.

47:54.480 --> 47:57.744
Infinite loneliness.

47:59.615 --> 48:02.618
And so, out of nothing,

48:05.143 --> 48:07.449
I created love.

48:09.843 --> 48:12.585
My greatest gift,
William.

48:12.628 --> 48:16.458
Allow me to take my throne

48:16.502 --> 48:18.896
and give it to you.

48:20.419 --> 48:24.336
Your family,
your little girl.

48:25.946 --> 48:28.383
I love them so.

48:30.995 --> 48:31.952
[CRYING]

48:34.563 --> 48:35.738
[VOICE BREAKS]
I know.

48:38.828 --> 48:42.397
What was taken

48:43.485 --> 48:46.358
shall now be returned.

48:49.709 --> 48:51.276
Stand aside,

48:53.060 --> 48:56.934
and let me
give you an eternity

48:58.674 --> 49:00.328
of love.

49:03.244 --> 49:04.463
What if

49:07.074 --> 49:09.163
[IN DISTORTED VOICE]
I choose hate?

49:20.392 --> 49:21.610
[GOD YELLS]

49:22.524 --> 49:24.091
[THUNDER RUMBLING]

50:03.348 --> 50:05.089
JOHN WAYNE: [ON SCREEN]
That's what's important.

50:05.132 --> 50:07.700
To feel useful
in this old world.

50:07.743 --> 50:09.702
To hit a lick
against what's wrong,

50:09.745 --> 50:11.834
or to say a word
for what's right,

50:11.878 --> 50:15.012
even though
you get walloped
for saying that word.

50:15.055 --> 50:18.145
Now, I may sound like
a Bible-beater
yelling up a revival

50:18.189 --> 50:20.191
at a river-crossing
camp meeting,

50:20.234 --> 50:22.019
but that don't change
the truth none.

50:22.062 --> 50:24.195
There's right,
and there's wrong.

50:24.238 --> 50:26.110
You got to do one
or the other.

50:26.153 --> 50:28.503
You do the one,
and you're living.

50:28.547 --> 50:30.592
You do the other,
and you may be
walking around,

50:30.636 --> 50:32.768
but you're dead
as a beaver hat.

50:45.607 --> 50:49.350
So I hear
you're a banker now.
Is that right?

50:49.872 --> 50:51.091
Well,

50:52.049 --> 50:54.312
I run an
asset management fund.

50:54.355 --> 50:57.489
We advise small businesses
on charitable giving,

50:57.532 --> 51:00.187
titling of assets,
and income
replacement strategies.

51:07.586 --> 51:09.588
I've been praying.
Yeah?

51:12.156 --> 51:14.071
Don't really
know why, but...

51:15.463 --> 51:16.812
Just have.

51:16.856 --> 51:17.900
Hmm.

51:17.944 --> 51:19.293
No, I get it.

51:20.338 --> 51:21.948
I think your daddy
would, too.

51:25.212 --> 51:26.605
You think?
Oh, yeah.

51:28.215 --> 51:30.391
He said you, uh,
used to drink gasoline...

51:30.435 --> 51:31.958
[CASSIDY CHUCKLES]

51:32.001 --> 51:35.788
...and killed 20 angels
with a chainsaw.
Is that true?

51:35.831 --> 51:39.096
No, that's not
bloody true.
He's exaggerating.

51:39.139 --> 51:41.141
It was
engine coolant.

51:41.185 --> 51:42.534
[LAUGHS]

51:42.577 --> 51:44.927
He says you were
the toughest guy
he ever met.

51:47.974 --> 51:49.367
Really?

51:49.410 --> 51:51.586
Yeah.

51:51.630 --> 51:53.153
That means a lot
coming from him.

51:54.198 --> 51:56.025
Mom, too.

51:56.069 --> 51:57.766
She talked about
you a lot.

51:57.810 --> 51:59.681
All the time, actually.

52:02.597 --> 52:05.992
Guess she wondered
why you never
came back to see them.

52:06.035 --> 52:07.950
I always meant to.
I just...

52:09.169 --> 52:10.779
I always...

52:10.823 --> 52:13.521
I run out of time.
You know?

52:14.131 --> 52:15.349
I get it.

52:18.787 --> 52:20.224
She loved you.

52:22.139 --> 52:23.183
Very much.

52:26.665 --> 52:29.668
Over 150 years,
and I've been
stabbed, bloody

52:31.409 --> 52:34.412
chopped up, blown up,
dropped out of airplanes,

52:34.455 --> 52:36.327
and I just,
I just kept going.

52:36.370 --> 52:39.112
Because that's what you do.
You just...

52:39.156 --> 52:40.635
You got to
pick yourself up,
you know?

52:40.679 --> 52:43.421
Just forget the pain,
try and carry on.

52:45.945 --> 52:48.339
But your bloody mom,

52:48.382 --> 52:50.776
did you know she shot me
twice in the chest?

52:50.819 --> 52:53.561
Right in the heart.
Two times.

52:55.998 --> 52:57.261
[CHILDREN YELLING]

52:57.304 --> 52:59.219
That was years ago.

53:00.438 --> 53:01.787
It still hurts.

53:03.963 --> 53:06.313
Guys, quit your messing,
and be respectful!

53:07.358 --> 53:08.924
I'm sorry.
Oh, it's all right.

53:11.144 --> 53:12.319
[SNIFFLES]

53:15.583 --> 53:16.802
I think
I'll get going.

53:16.845 --> 53:18.586
Where to now?

53:18.630 --> 53:20.893
Bangkok? Tijuana?

53:20.936 --> 53:23.548
Always did love hearing
about your adventures.

53:23.591 --> 53:24.723
Hmm. No way.

53:27.291 --> 53:29.467
I think I'll try
someplace new.

53:35.603 --> 53:36.604
All right.

53:38.519 --> 53:39.607
Mr. Cassidy?

53:42.262 --> 53:43.698
We ever see you again?

53:49.356 --> 53:50.531
Jesus, I hope so.

53:56.058 --> 53:58.278
♪ And I will
stroll the merry way

53:58.322 --> 54:00.019
♪ And jump the hedges first

54:03.762 --> 54:06.243
♪ And I will drink
the clear clean water

54:06.286 --> 54:07.940
♪ For to quench my thirst

54:12.553 --> 54:14.599
♪ And I shall
watch the ferry-boats

54:14.642 --> 54:16.601
♪ And they'll get high

54:20.909 --> 54:22.955
♪ On a blue ocean

54:22.998 --> 54:25.958
♪ Against tomorrow's sky

54:29.222 --> 54:32.878
♪ And I will never grow
so old again

54:37.535 --> 54:42.366
♪ And I will walk and talk
in gardens
all wet with rain

54:49.198 --> 54:52.332
♪ Oh, sweet thing,
sweet thing ♪
